One thing I see from the list above is that a majority of them end in "URI".  Considering that I got "URI properties must end in URI" into the standard, could we make this more resilient to added properties, and OEM properties with something like:

std::array<std::string_view, X> nonUriProperties{
   "@odata.id"
   ,...
}

if (boost::iendswith(propertyName, "uri") || std::binary_search(nonUriProperties.begin(), nonUriProperties.end(), propertyName) != nonUriProperties.end()){

}


That keeps us relatively future proof, so long as Redfish doesn't add any URI properties that don't end in URI (which they've now been informed to not) and when OEM properties add a URI, that will get aggregated properly as well?
